# .cursorindexingignore — exclude from indexing / codebase search ONLY.
# https://cursor.com/docs/reference/ignore-file
#
# Unlike .cursorignore, files listed here STAY readable by Agent, Tab, and Inline Edit —
# they just won't surface in semantic codebase search. Use for large, generated, or
# vendored files that add noise to search but that the agent may occasionally need to open
# (e.g. read a Worker binding type, check a pinned dependency version).
#
# Gitignored build outputs and dependencies (node_modules/, dist/, .turbo/, caches) are
# already excluded from indexing by Cursor's automatic .gitignore handling; the build/cache
# globs below are listed only as explicit, self-documenting belt-and-suspenders.

# Committed lockfile — huge, low signal, but sometimes read to confirm a resolved version
pnpm-lock.yaml

# Generated type declarations — regenerated by `make types`; readable but not search-worthy
**/worker-configuration.d.ts
**/vite-env.d.ts
**/*.d.ts.map

# Agent skills — loaded on demand by name (via SKILL.md frontmatter), never surfaced through
# codebase search. The vendored trees alone carry ~100 rule/reference markdown files
# (vercel-react-best-practices ~70, ui-ux-design 16, turborepo/workers references, tanstack, …)
# that would otherwise flood semantic search with framework guidance unrelated to app code.
# De-indexed here but still fully readable/loadable — .cursorindexingignore only drops files
# from search, not from Agent/Tab/Inline-Edit access. `.claude/skills/*` are symlinks into
# `.agents/skills/`; both paths are listed so neither indexing route re-adds the noise.
.agents/skills/**
.claude/skills/**

# Generated database migration artifacts (SQL + JSON snapshots)
**/drizzle/migrations/**

# Build outputs & caches (also gitignored — listed to guarantee they never reach the index)
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.turbo/
**/.wrangler/
**/.flue-vite/
**/.tanstack/
**/.vite/
**/coverage/
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.map
